  "conclusion": "1. Interval development of cytotoxic edema in the parietal lobes bilaterally, right greater than left, likely sequela of known ischemia.\n2. There is a new punctate focus of hyperdensity in the high left frontal lobe. It could represent small focus of subarachnoid hemorrhage versus residual intravascular contrast. Short-term follow-up is suggested.",
